Young Bachelor (Vincent)
James is a 27-year-old bachelor, working full time in a marketing role just outside of Green Bay. James grew up in Appleton, where his father worked 
as a construction manager, and his mother worked as a receptionist at a local company. His family is supportive, but practical, and values saving and 
future planning.  He started this job 3 years ago, just after graduating with a bachelor’s degree in marketing from UW-Green Bay. He pays $650 in rent 
for a two-bedroom apartment that he shares with his one roommate, a 30-year-old man. The two-split electricity, water and Wi-Fi bills. He drives to 
work every day in a used car for which he pay $350 monthly, and $100 in insurance. He goes out with friends most weekends and attends many concerts. 
Additionally, James pays for several streaming services (Netflix, Spotify, Disney+). Recently, he has felt pressured by his bills and as a result,  
James has recently begun to manage his budget a little closer, and wants to set up a saving plan.


Vincent's user stories:
When Vincent logs into the system, the system shall display his monthly income, fixed expenses, and remaining discretionary income in a clear dashboard. 
When he records shared bills, the system shall calculate only his portion of the expense. 
While his spending approaches or exceeds his monthly budget, the system shall generate a notification alert. When Vincent sets a savings goal, the system shall calculate and track his required monthly contribution. 
The system shall categorize discretionary expenses, such as dining and entertainment, to help him monitor spending trends.
